---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SidebarCTA from '../../components/SidebarCTA.astro';
---

<link slot="head" rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;0,700;1,400;1,600&display=swap" />
<style>
  :root { --font-family-heading: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif; }
</style>

<Layout
  title="About Numerology Guides & Maddie Greene | Numerology Guides"
  description="The story behind Numerology Guides. How a painful divorce at 23 led Maddie Greene to numerology, and why she built a free resource to help others find the same clarity."
>
  <!-- Page header -->
  <section style="background:var(--color-light-bg);padding:4rem 1.5rem 3.5rem;position:relative;overflow:hidden;border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border);">
    <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background-image:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(124,92,191,0.07) 1px,transparent 1px);background-size:28px 28px;pointer-events:none;"></div>
    <div style="position:relative;z-index:1;max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;text-align:center;">
      <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-family-heading);font-size:clamp(2rem,5vw,3.25rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--color-body-text);margin:0 0 1rem;">
        About <span style="color:var(--color-soft-gold);">Numerology Guides</span>
      </h1>
      <p style="color:var(--color-muted-text);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.7;margin:0;">
        The short version: a broken marriage, a friend's offhand suggestion, and fifteen years of connecting dots.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content + Sticky sidebar wrapper -->
  <div class="xl:flex xl:gap-6 xl:max-w-[1200px] xl:mx-auto xl:px-4">
    <!-- Main content column -->
    <div class="xl:flex-1 xl:min-w-0">

  <!-- Content -->
  <section style="padding:2.5rem 1rem;background:white;">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto xl:mx-0 xl:max-w-none space-y-6">

      <!-- Maddie's story -->
      <div class="card-light p-6 md:p-8">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <img src="/images/author-maddi-green.webp" alt="Maddie Greene" class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full object-cover border-2 border-violet/20 shadow-sm" />
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-family-heading)] text-body-text">Maddie Greene</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted-text">Founder, Numerology Guides</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-family-heading)] text-body-text mb-4">How it started</h3>

        <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
          I got married at 22. By 23 it was over. A year and a half, start to finish. The relationship was bad early on, but I didn't see it at the time. I just felt like I was slowly disappearing. Smaller every month, less sure of what I actually wanted.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
          After the divorce I moved back in with my parents and got a retail job I didn't care about. Most nights I'd sit on the couch and just scroll my phone until it was late enough to go to bed. If you'd asked me what I liked, what I was good at, what kind of life I wanted, I wouldn't have had an answer for any of it. The marriage had kind of worn all that away.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
          My friend Sarah kept telling me to "look into my numbers." I thought she meant budgeting. She meant numerology. I rolled my eyes the first few times. Eventually I was bored enough and low enough to try it.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
          I looked up how to calculate a life path number. Did the math. Read the description. And I just sat there for a while. It wasn't vague horoscope stuff. It described a pattern I'd been living out without ever naming it. My soul urge number basically spelled out the thing I'd been suppressing for the whole marriage. My expression number pointed at strengths I'd completely forgotten I had.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
          I didn't convert overnight. But I got curious, and that was the first time I'd felt curious about anything in months.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-family-heading)] text-body-text mb-4 mt-8">What the numbers did for me</h3>

        <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
          I started reading everything I could find about Pythagorean numerology. Not as a hobby. I wanted to understand what was going on with me. The more I learned, the more things clicked. Like why I kept taking jobs that looked good on paper but made me miserable. Or why certain friendships felt draining from day one.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The numbers didn't fix my life. But they gave me a way to look at myself that didn't feel like therapy or self-help or someone listing what was wrong with me. More like, "here's the pattern. Now what do you want to do about it?"
        </p>
        <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Over the next couple of years, things got better. I quit the retail job, stopped saying yes to people who made me feel small, slowly stopped second-guessing every decision. The numbers didn't give me confidence. They just helped me remember who I was before I lost track of it.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-family-heading)] text-body-text mb-4 mt-8">Fifteen years later</h3>

        <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
          That was fifteen years ago. I'm 38 now. Somewhere along the way I became the person friends call when they're going through something and can't figure out why they keep ending up in the same spot. I've done charts for friends, coworkers, my mom's book club. The reaction is almost always the same. Someone looks at their numbers, goes quiet, and says "wait, that's... yeah. That's it."
        </p>
        <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
          I built this site because most numerology content online is either so vague it could apply to anyone, or so dressed up in mysticism it's hard to take seriously. I wanted something I would've found useful at 23, sitting on my parents' couch, wondering what was wrong with me. Something free that actually explains the system.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed">
          Nothing was wrong with me. I just didn't know myself yet.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- What the site covers -->
      <div class="card-light p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-family-heading)] text-body-text mb-3">
          <span class="text-violet mr-2">⬥</span> What you'll find here
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-4">Every guide on this site uses the Pythagorean system, the most widely practiced approach in Western numerology. The content covers:</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" class="text-rpg-green mt-1 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
            <div class="text-muted-text">
              <span class="text-body-text font-semibold">Life path numbers 1 through 9</span>, plus master numbers 11, 22, and 33
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" class="text-rpg-green mt-1 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
            <div class="text-muted-text">
              <span class="text-body-text font-semibold">All five core chart numbers</span>: life path, expression, soul urge, personality, and birthday
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" class="text-rpg-green mt-1 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
            <div class="text-muted-text">
              <span class="text-body-text font-semibold">Compatibility for all 78 life path pairs</span>, with real insights about love, friendship, and work
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" class="text-rpg-green mt-1 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
            <div class="text-muted-text">
              <span class="text-body-text font-semibold">Advanced topics</span>: karmic debt numbers, pinnacle cycles, challenge numbers, maturity numbers, and personal year cycles
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" class="text-rpg-green mt-1 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
            <div class="text-muted-text">
              <span class="text-body-text font-semibold">Free tools</span>: a numerology calculator and an interactive compatibility checker
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Approach -->
      <div class="card-light p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-family-heading)] text-body-text mb-3">
          <span class="text-violet mr-2">⬥</span> How I write about numerology
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-3">
          I don't do predictions. Numerology isn't fortune-telling, at least not how I use it. Your numbers describe patterns and tendencies. They don't tell you what's going to happen. You still get to decide that part.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Everything on this site is written the way I'd explain it if you asked me about it over coffee. I try to be honest about what the numbers suggest, including the parts that aren't flattering. If a number has a difficult side, I'll say so. I'll also tell you what to do about it, because there's always something you can do.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed">
          I also try not to make any of this more mystical than it needs to be. The subject is interesting enough without dressing it up.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Recommended reading -->
      <div class="card-light p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-family-heading)] text-body-text mb-3">
          <span class="text-violet mr-2">⬥</span> Want your numbers applied to you specifically?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed">
          The guides here explain how numerology works in general. If you want your specific numbers calculated and interpreted for you, I'd point you to <strong class="text-body-text">Numerologist.com</strong>. They've been around since 1999 and they do a free personalized video reading based on your name and birth date. It's what I tell friends to try when they want something more personal than a general guide.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mt-3">
          Full transparency: I'm an affiliate, which means I earn a commission if you purchase a paid report after the free reading. The free video itself costs nothing. And I wouldn't recommend something I haven't used myself.
        </p>
        <a
          href="https://8904b5z1168aar3k8annz7y61n.hop.clickbank.net"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener sponsored"
          style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:var(--color-violet);color:white;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:6px;text-decoration:none;margin-top:1rem;"
        >
          Get a Free Reading at Numerologist.com
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <div class="card-light p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-family-heading)] text-body-text mb-3">
          <span class="text-violet mr-2">⬥</span> Get in touch
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed">
          Questions, corrections, or just want to say hi?
          <a href="mailto:hello@numerologyguides.blog" class="text-violet hover:underline font-medium">hello@numerologyguides.blog</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center pt-4">
        <a href="/learn/" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:var(--color-violet);color:white;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:6px;text-decoration:none;">Browse the Free Guides →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

    </div><!-- end main content column -->
    <SidebarCTA />
  </div><!-- end flex wrapper -->
</Layout>
